{"title_page": "1992 NC State Wolfpack football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| sport = football\n| year = 1992  |team=NC State Wolfpack\n| image=North Carolina State University Athletic logo.svg\n| image_size=100\n| conference=Atlantic Coast Conference\n| short_conf=ACC\n| CoachRank = 15\n| APRank = 17\n| record = 9\u20133\u20131\n| conf_record = 6\u20132\n| head_coach = [[Dick Sheridan]]\n| hc_year = 7th\n| off_coach = \n| oc_year = \n| def_coach = \n| dc_year = \n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| stadium = [[Carter\u2013Finley Stadium]]<br/>(Capacity: 51,500)\n| champion = \n| bowl = [[1992 Gator Bowl|Gator Bowl]]\n| bowl_result = L 10\u201327 vs. [[1992 Florida Gators football team|Florida]]\n| conf_champ = \n| conf_champ_result = \n}}\n{{1992 ACC football standings}}\nThe '''1992 NC State Wolfpack football team''' represented [[North Carolina State University]] during the [[1992 NCAA Division I-A football season]]. The team's head coach was [[Dick Sheridan]]. NC State has been a member of the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC) since the league's inception in 1953. The Wolfpack played its home games in 1992 at [[Carter\u2013Finley Stadium]] in [[Raleigh, North Carolina]], which has been NC State football's home stadium since 1966.\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1992\n| poll = AP\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = August 29\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| neutral = y\n| rank = \n| opponent = [[1992 Iowa Hawkeyes football team|Iowa]]\n| opprank = 16\n| gamename = [[Kickoff Classic]]\n| site_stadium = [[Giants Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[East Rutherford, New Jersey|East Rutherford, NJ]]\n| score = 24\u201314\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 5\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 18\n| opponent = [[1992 Appalachian State Mountaineers football team|Appalachian State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Carter\u2013Finley Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]]\n| score = 35\u201310\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 12\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| rank = 19\n| opponent = [[1992 Maryland Terrapins football team|Maryland]]\n| site_stadium = [[Byrd Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[College Park, Maryland|College Park, MD]]\n| score = 14\u201310\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 19\n| w/l = l\n| rank = 16\n| opponent = [[1992 Florida State Seminoles football team|Florida State]]\n| opprank = 3\n| site_stadium = Carter\u2013Finley Stadium\n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| score = 13\u201334\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 26\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| rank = 23\n| opponent = [[1992 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| gamename = [[North Carolina\u2013NC State football rivalry|rivalry]]\n| site_stadium = [[Kenan Memorial Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Chapel Hill, North Carolina|Chapel Hill, NC]]\n| score = 27\u201320\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 3\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| rank = 21\n| opponent = [[1992 Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football team|Georgia Tech]]\n| opprank = 23\n| site_stadium = [[Bobby Dodd Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Atlanta|Atlanta, GA]]\n| score = 13\u201316\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 10\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 25\n| opponent = [[1992 Texas Tech Red Raiders football team|Texas Tech]]\n| site_stadium = Carter\u2013Finley Stadium\n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n| score = 48\u201313\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 17\n| w/l = t\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| rank = 21\n| opponent = [[1992 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|Virginia Tech]]\n| site_stadium = [[Lane Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Blacksburg, Virginia|Blacksburg, VA]]\n| score = 13\u201313\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 24\n| w/l = w\n| rank = 23\n| opponent = [[1992 Clemson Tigers football team|Clemson]]\n| opprank = 18\n| gamename = [[Textile Bowl]]\n| site_stadium = Carter\u2013Finley Stadium\n| site_cityst = Raleigh, NC\n|