{"title_page": "1990\u201391 UNLV Runnin' Rebels basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season  \n|sport        =Basketball  \n|year         =1990\u201391  \n|prev_year    = 1989\u201390  \n|next_year    = 1991\u201392  \n|team         =UNLV Runnin' Rebels  \n|image        =  \n|image_size   =  \n|conference   =Big West Conference  \n|division     =  \n|short_conf   =Big West  \n|CoachRank    =1   \n|APRank       = 1  \n|record       =  34\u20131  \n|conf_record  = 18\u20130  \n|head_coach   =[[Jerry Tarkanian]]  \n|hc_year      =18th  \n|asst_coach1  =[[Tim Grgurich]]  \n|asst_coach2  =[[Ron Ganulin]]  \n|ac2_year     =4th  \n|asst_coach3  =Cleveland Edwards  \n|stadium      =[[Thomas and Mack Center]]  \n|champion     =[[1991 Big West Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|Big West Tournament Champions]]<br>Big West Regular Season Champions  \n|bowl         =[[1991 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|NCAA Men's Division I Tournament]]  \n|bowl_result  = [[1991 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|Final Four]]\n}}\n{{1990\u201391 Big West basketball standings}}\nThe '''1990\u201391 UNLV Runnin' Rebels basketball team''' represented the [[University of Nevada, Las Vegas]] in  [[NCAA Division I]] men's [[college basketball|competition]] in the [[1990\u201391 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|1990\u201391 season]]. The Runnin' Rebels, coached by [[Jerry Tarkanian]], entered the season as [[1989\u201390 UNLV Runnin' Rebels basketball team|defending national champions]] and entered the [[1991 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1991 NCAA tournament]] unbeaten, but lost in the national semifinal to eventual champions [[1990\u201391 Duke Blue Devils men's basketball team|Duke]] when [[Anderson Hunt]]'s desperation three in the final seconds bounced off the backboard and into the hands of a Duke player, [[Bobby Hurley]], ending a 45-game winning streak that dated back to the previous season. They had been the last team to [[Perfect season#NCAA Division I Basketball|finish the regular season unbeaten]] before [[2003\u201304 Saint Joseph's Hawks men's basketball team|St. Joseph's]] did it in 2004. They were the last team to enter the NCAA tournament unbeaten until [[2013\u201314 Wichita State Shockers men's basketball team|Wichita State]] did it in 2014 and [[2014\u201315 Kentucky Wildcats men's basketball team|Kentucky]] in 2015.\n\nThe team played its home games in the [[Thomas & Mack Center]], and was a member of the [[Big West Conference]]; it would join the [[Western Athletic Conference]] in 1996 and become a charter member of its current conference, the [[Mountain West Conference]], in 1999.\n\nThe nickname \"Runnin' Rebels\" is unique to men's basketball at UNLV. The default nickname for men's sports teams at the school is simply \"Rebels\", while all women's teams are known as \"Lady Rebels\".\n\n==Roster==\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=1990|team=UNLV Runnin' Rebels|teamcolors=y}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Larry|last=Johnson|num=4|pos=F|ft=6|in=7|lbs=250|class=Sr|rs=|link=y|dab=basketball, born 1969|home=[[Dallas, Texas|Dallas, TX]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Anderson|last=Hunt|num=12|pos=G|ft=6|in=1|lbs=180|class=Jr|rs=|link=y|home=[[Detroit, Michigan|Detroit, MI]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Travis|last=Bice|num=13|pos=G|ft=6|in=4|lbs=155|class=Jr|rs=|home=[[Simi Valley, California|Simi Valley, CA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Bryan|last=Emerzian|num=15|pos=G|ft=5|in=11|lbs=160|class=Jr|rs=|home=[[Waukegan, Illinois|Waukegan, IL]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Elmore|last=Spencer|num=24|pos=C|ft=7|in=0|lbs=265|class=Jr|rs=|link=y|home=[[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta, GA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Dave|last=Rice|num=30|pos=G|ft=6|in=4|lbs=205|class=Sr|rs=|link=y|dab=basketball|home=[[Claremont, California|Claremont, CA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Stacey|last=Augmon|num=32|pos=F|ft=6|in=8|lbs=210|class=Sr|rs=|link=y|home=[[Pasadena, California|Pasadena, CA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Barry|last=Young|num=33|pos=G/F|ft=6|in=7|lbs=200|class=Sr|rs=|home=[[Ellicott City, Maryland|Ellicott City, MD]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=George|last=Ackles|num=44|pos=F/C|ft=6|in=9|lbs=210|class=Sr|rs=y|link=y|home=[[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania|Pittsburgh, PA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Greg|last=Anthony|num=50|pos=G|ft=6|in=0|lbs=175|class=Sr|rs=|link=y|home=[[Las Vegas, Nevada|Las Vegas, NV]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Chris|last=Jeter|num=53|pos=F|ft=6|in=8|lbs=215|class=Sr|rs=|home=[[San Diego, California|San Diego, CA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Sean|last=Watkins|num=|pos=G|ft=|in=|lbs=|class=So|rs=|home=&nbsp;}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Byron|last=Wesley|num=|pos=F|ft=|in=|lbs=|class=Sr|rs=|home=&nbsp;}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Dan|last=Bisek|num=|pos=G|ft=|in=|lbs=|class=Sr|rs=|home=&nbsp;}}\n{{CBB roster/Footer\n|head_coach=\n* [[Jerry Tarkanian]] ({{college|[[Fresno State University|Fresno State]]}})\n|asst_coach=\n* \n|roster_url=\n|accessdate=\n}}\n[https://www.sports-reference.com/cbb/schools/nevada-las-vegas/1991.html]\n\n==Schedule and results==\n{{CBB schedule start|gamehighs=yes|rank=|attend=yes}}\n|-\n!colspan=12 style={{NCAA color cell|UNLV Runnin' Rebels}}| Regular Season\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date         = Dec 1, 1990\n| time         = \n| w/l          = w\n| nonconf      = yes\n| away         = \n| neutral      = yes\n| rank         = 1\n| opponent     = {{cbb link|year=1990|sex=men|team=UAB Blazers|title=Alabama-Birmingham}}\n| opprank      = \n| site_stadium = \n| site_cityst  = [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia|BC]]\n| gamename     = \n| score        = 109\u201368\n| overtime     = \n| highscorer    = Johnson\n| points        = 26\n| highrebounder = &nbsp;\n| rebounds      = &nbsp;\n| highassister  = &nbsp;\n| assists       = &nbsp;\n| attend       = \n| record       = 1\u20130\n}}\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date         = Dec 7, 1990\n| time         = \n| w/l      